<subSubSection pageId="59" pageNumber="60" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="59.[151,1436,151,285]" pageId="59" pageNumber="60">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,151,176]" pageId="59" pageNumber="60">Remarks.</emphasis>
This new species differs from 
<taxonomicName authority="Santos &amp; Azevedo, 2000" authorityName="Santos &amp; Azevedo" authorityYear="2000" box="[666,1115,151,176]" class="Insecta" family="Bethylidae" genus="Anisepyris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="59" pageNumber="60" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="breviramus">
<emphasis box="[666,824,151,176]" italics="true" pageId="59" pageNumber="60">A. breviramus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation box="[832,1115,151,176]" pageId="59" pageNumber="60" refId="ref281771" refString="Santos, H. S. &amp; Azevedo, C. O. (2000) Sistematica das especies de Anisepyris Kieffer (Hymenoptera, Bethylidae) do Brasil. Revista Brasileira de Entomologia, 44, 129 - 165." type="journal article">Santos &amp; Azevedo, 2000</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
only by having the pronotal disc with its transverse pronotal carina incomplete and the basal portion of the paramere narrow, whereas 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Santos &amp; Azevedo" authorityYear="2000" class="Insecta" family="Bethylidae" genus="Anisepyris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="59" pageNumber="60" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="breviramus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="59" pageNumber="60">A. breviramus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has the pronotal disc with its transverse pronotal carina complete; and with the basal portion of the paramere wide.
</paragraph>
